      • recreateAnnotatedTypeForEquals

        public static AnnotatedType recreateAnnotatedTypeForEquals(AnnotatedType type)
        Create a new instance from or return the provided AnnotatedType based on whether it has a usable Object.equals(Object) implementation. One such example is the standard JDK implementations, as they do not implement Object.equals(Object) properly until Java 12. Any type that does not have a proper equals implementation cannot be utilized as the left hand side of an equals operation.
        Parameters:
        type - AnnotatedType to recreate as necessary for a usable Object.equals(Object) implementation.
        Returns:
        type or a copy of it with a usable Object.equals(Object) implementation.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException -
        • When type is null
        • When type does not represent a supported AnnotatedType

      • recreateAnnotatedTypesForEquals

        public static AnnotatedType[] recreateAnnotatedTypesForEquals(AnnotatedType... types)
        Create a new instances from or return the provided AnnotatedTypes based on whether they have usable Object.equals(Object) implementations. As the standard JDK implementations do not implement Object.equals(Object) properly they cannot be utilized as the left hand side of an equals operation.
        Parameters:
        types - AnnotatedTypes to recreate as necessary for a usable Object.equals(Object) implementation.
        Returns:
        types or a copy of it with a usable Object.equals(Object) implementation.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException -
        • When types is null
        • When types contains a null
        • When any type element does not represent a supported AnnotatedType
